M||tx|---
M||titl|Use useRef for Transient Values
M||impa|md
M||impa|avoids unnecessary re-renders on frequent updates
M||tags|rerender, useref, state, perf
M||tx|---
M|Use |tx|When a value changes frequently and you don't want a re-render on every up (e.g., mouse trackers, intervals, transient flags), store it in `useRef` instead of `useState`. Keep cp state for UI; use refs for temporary DOM-adjacent values. Updating a ref does not trigger a re-render.
M|Use |**In|**
M|Use |tx|```tsx
M|Use |tx|fn Tracker() {
M|Use |tx|const [lastX, setLastX] = useState(0)
M|Use |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|Use |cons|MouseEvent) => setLastX(e.clientX)
M|Use |tx|window.addEventListener('mousemove', onMove)
M|Use |tx|return () => window.removeEventListener('mousemove', onMove)
M|Use |tx|}, [])
M|Use |tx|return (
M|Use |tx|<div
M|Use |tx|style={{
M|Use |posi|'fixed',
M|Use |top|0,
M|Use |left|lastX,
M|Use |widt|8,
M|Use |heig|8,
M|Use |back|'black',
M|Use |tx|}}
M|Use |tx|/>
M|Use |tx|)
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|```
M|Use |**Co|**
M|Use |tx|```tsx
M|Use |tx|fn Tracker() {
M|Use |tx|const lastXRef = useRef(0)
M|Use |tx|const dotRef = useRef<HTMLDivElement>(null)
M|Use |tx|useEffect(() => {
M|Use |cons|MouseEvent) => {
M|Use |tx|lastXRef.current = e.clientX
M|Use |tx|const node = dotRef.current
M|Use |tx|if (node) {
M|Use |tx|node.style.transform = `translateX(${e.clientX}px)`
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|window.addEventListener('mousemove', onMove)
M|Use |tx|return () => window.removeEventListener('mousemove', onMove)
M|Use |tx|}, [])
M|Use |tx|return (
M|Use |tx|<div
M|Use |tx|ref={dotRef}
M|Use |tx|style={{
M|Use |posi|'fixed',
M|Use |top|0,
M|Use |left|0,
M|Use |widt|8,
M|Use |heig|8,
M|Use |back|'black',
M|Use |tran|'translateX(0px)',
M|Use |tx|}}
M|Use |tx|/>
M|Use |tx|)
M|Use |tx|}
M|Use |tx|```